For instance, if you give your program an instance field, say, `selectedButton` that held a reference to the last selected button, then any ActionListener&#39;s response can vary depending on what this field holds. The first time any JButton is pressed, this field will hold `null` since no previous JButton was pressed, and so the ActionListener will assign this button to that field. The second time that the ActionListener is called (the second time that a JButton is pressed), the field will hold a value, and so, using an if / else block that checks the state of this field, the listener&#39;s behavior can vary:

